Rest Assured works on three basic principles --

Given -- All Input details - headers/query and path parameter/body/ log().all() for input
When -- Submit the API with HTTP Method/resource name
Then -- Validate the response -- assertion / log().all() for output

JSONPath is a class which takes string as input and convert that into json format as output and to parse JSON.

size() is a method in jsonpath which return count. It is only used with array.


************************Libraryapi -- DynamicJson.java
Files.readAllBytes(Path path) --> read content of file and convert it to bytes format and then
bytes to string-- for converting bytes to string -- need to wrap input with new sting()...
it receives path of file as path class such ass -->Paths.get("")


